    "department": "GTM",
    "description": "About the Company\n\nWhy We Built Lyric: Supply chains are more critical and complex than ever. Every day, large enterprises navigate trillions of possible decisions that could impact the bottom line. Powerful algorithms and AI can address these problems, yet most organizations struggle to leverage supply chain AI at scale. The current SCM technologies are either rigid, limited-scope point solutions or custom solutions built in-house, which demand immense expertise and investment.\n\nThat is…until now.\n\nEnter Lyric: Lyric is an enterprise AI platform built specifically for supply chains, offering the best of both worlds:\n\n - Out-of-the-box AI solutions for optimizing networks, allocating inventory, scheduling routes, planning fulfillment capacity, promising orders, propagating demand, building predictions, analyzing scenarios, and more, plus\n\n - A platform-first approach that empowers both business and technical users with end-to-end product composability, leveraging no-code tools, their own code, or even forking our code to build and refine supply chain decision intelligence\n\nWith Lyric, enterprises no longer have to choose between flexibility and speed, they get both.\n\nThe Mission: We’re building a new era in supply chain with the team best equipped to lead it. With over 20 years at the intersection of supply chain and algorithms, we developed a deep conviction that global supply chains needed something like Lyric. Since our inception in December 2021, that conviction has been validated time and time again.\n\nToday, a growing number of Fortune 500 companies, including Smurfit WestRock, Estée Lauder, Coca-Cola, and more, are innovating on their own terms with Lyric. We can’t wait to see what our customers, both current and future, are empowered to build with us next. Come build with us!\n\nAbout the Role\n\nLyric is hiring a VP of Marketing to scale our marketing function as a core member of the GTM leadership team. This is a senior, high-ownership role for a strong generalist who can set strategy, build teams, and execute across the full marketing mix.\n\nThe right candidate has a proven track record at high-growth B2B SaaS or enterprise AI companies and knows how to market complex technical solutions to Fortune 500/1000 buyers, connect storytelling to revenue, and build the systems and teams needed to grow.\n\nWhat You'll Do\n\n - Own Lyric's marketing execution across demand generation, field marketing, and content/brand, with a clear mandate to drive qualified pipeline and revenue growth\n\n - Build and lead a modern, always-on demand generation engine leveraging AI, automation, and data to optimize channel mix, targeting, and campaign performance across the funnel, with a sharp focus on enterprise buyers\n\n - Establish and evolve the marketing tech stack and data infrastructure, ensuring the right mix of tools for automation, lead scoring, content management, and reporting\n\n - Define the operating cadence for Marketing, including dashboards, forecasting, and business reviews, and partner with Sales using pipeline math to align on goals, diagnose gaps, and drive accountability\n\n - Build, develop, and coach a high-performing marketing team; evaluate talent honestly, place people in positions to succeed, and hold the organization to a high bar\n\n - Manage external partners across PR, brand/creative, and digital to maximize quality and efficiency\n\nAbout You\n\n - 10–15+ years of progressive marketing experience in B2B SaaS or enterprise AI/ML, with at least 5+ years building and leading marketing teams at high-growth companies\n\n - Strong generalist background spanning demand generation, product marketing, field marketing, and content/brand, with a proven ability to connect storytelling to revenue\n\n - Proven track record of marketing complex technical solutions to Fortune 500/1000 enterprises across the full buyer journey\n\n - Deep knowledge of B2B buyer journeys, marketing automation, and CRM systems (e.g., HubSpot); a modern marketer who embraces experimentation and stays ahead of emerging tools and tactics\n\n - Metrics-driven operator with a strong track record of hitting pipeline and revenue targets, and the budgeting and forecasting discipline to back it up\n\n - Demonstrated success managing and consolidating external partners across PR, creative, and digital\n\n - Excellent communicator and team builder who thrives in early-stage, high-visibility environments\n\nEven if you don't meet 100% of the qualifications, we recommend applying to the role!\n\nLocation: Remote - US. Some travel is required.\n\nCompensation: The annual on-target earnings for this role is $300K. Base cash will be determined based on years of experience, with an additional variable compensation that is earned based on individual \u0026 business performance. You will also receive equity in Lyric.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
